{"name": "odoo-version-manager", "metadata": {"name": "odoo-version-manager", "version": "0.0.12", "classifiers": [], "home_page": "https://github.com/odoo-module-version-manager.git", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Manage Versions of module along all odoo version", "upload_time": 1732800277}, "documentation": ["\n# odoo-version-manager\n\nHelps handling updates on main branch of a module to be deployed to all sub branches.\nIt uses github workflows to accomplish this.\n\n## installing\n\n```bash\npipx install odoo-version-manager\nodoo-version-manager completion -x\n```\n\n# usage\n\n## initial setup\n\n- create a repository like an OCA repository with some modules on branch **main**\n- decide which version the main branch is for example 16.0\n\n```\nodoo-version-manager setup 16.0\n```\n\n## set another odoo version for main branch\n\nIf you move on and main branch becomes odoo version 18.0 instead of 16.0 do the following:\n\n```\ngit checkout main\ngit reset --hard origin/18.0\nvi .github/version_behind_main_branch and set 18.0 there\nodoo-version-manager setup\n```\n\n## rebase all branches\n\nIf there are merge conflicts you must manually help the branches to pass there new commits from one to the other.\nIt is advised to use the -r option to reduce the commits from one branch to the other to make it easier the next time to resolve merge conflicts.\n\n```\nodoo-version-manager rebase -r\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "odoo_version_manager.filelock", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "odoo_version_manager.filelock.FileLockException", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "odoo_version_manager.filelock.FileLock", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "odoo_version_manager.filelock.FileLock.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "file_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "timeout", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "delay", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Prepare the file locker. Specify the file to lock and optionally\nthe maximum timeout and the delay between each attempt to lock."]}, {"name": "odoo_version_manager.filelock.FileLock.acquire", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Acquire the lock, if possible. If the lock is in use, it check again\nevery `wait` seconds. It does this until it either gets the lock or\nexceeds `timeout` number of seconds, in which case it throws\nan exception."]}, {"name": "odoo_version_manager.filelock.FileLock.release", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Get rid of the lock by deleting the lockfile.\nWhen working in a `with` statement, this gets automatically\ncalled at the end.", "self.is_locked = True"]}, {"name": "odoo_version_manager.filelock.FileLock.__enter__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Activated when used in the with statement.\nShould automatically acquire a lock to be used in the with block."]}, {"name": "odoo_version_manager.filelock.FileLock.__exit__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "type", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "traceback", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Activated at the end of the with statement.\nIt automatically releases the lock if it isn't locked."]}, {"name": "odoo_version_manager.filelock.FileLock.__del__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Make sure that t